RMER

This is an utility program. It removes files from the filesystem after a
specified delay. All input to the program is on STDIN and is in the form of a
special protocol (not user friendly).

Synopsis:
$ rmer [-if <infile>] [-D] [-V]

Arguments:
-if <infile>	alternative to STDIN
-D		turns on debugging to standard-error
-V		print program version to standard-error and then exit

